First of all, when a player starts mining, we calculate the number of blocks mined
per minute in the last 5 minutes.
Here is an example to explain.
The player logs in, then begins to mine land. To know the price, we collect all the
broken Dirt blocks during the last 5 minutes. In our example, 20 blocks of dirt have
been mined in the last 5 minutes. We calculate the time between the last mined block
and the frst mined block that is not more than 5 minutes.
Let's imagine that the frst block was mined at 900 am exactly and that the last
one was mined at 903 am. So it's been 3 minutes
We can then calculate how many blocks of Dirt the player has mined per minute by
doing one of these two calculations :
if the elapsed time in minutes is smaller than or equal to 1
if the elapsed time in minute is greater than 1
Here we have 20 / 3 which makes 6.66 blocks per minute
Now you have to know that for the dirt block, its maximum value of BlocPerMinute is
200. This means that if the player exceeds 200 blocks per minute, he will not win
